<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd"><html>



<head>



<title>DIE-WHEN-TOO-OLD</title>

</head>



<body>

	<h3><i>I die when I get too old.</i> </h3>

	<p><font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	</p>
	<p><b>DIE-WHEN-TOO-OLD </b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>when [time - my-birth &gt; my-maximum-life]
     [add-behaviour <a title="DIE" href="DIE.html">DIE</a>]
</pre>

	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2><span class="mw-headline">Variants </span></h2>

	<p>You can change this to add behaviours other than <i>die</i> when an age 

	is exceeded. </p>

	<h2><span class="mw-headline">Related Micro-behaviours </span></h2>

	<p>

	<a title="AGE-IS-ZERO" href="AGE-IS-ZERO.html">

	AGE-IS-ZERO</a> should be used to record the time of birth.

	<a title="DIE-WHEN-TOO-HUNGRY" href="DIE-WHEN-TOO-HUNGRY.html">

	DIE-WHEN-TOO-HUNGRY</a> has a similar function but uses <i>my-hunger</i> 

	rather than computing my age by subtracting <i>my-birth</i> from now. </p>

	<h2><span class="mw-headline">How this works </span></h2>

	<p>When the difference between now and <i>my-birth</i> exceeds a number set 

	by

	<a title="SET-MAXIMUM-LIFE" href="SET-MAXIMUM-LIFE.html">

	SET-MAXIMUM-LIFE</a> then I add the

	<a title="DIE" href="DIE.html">DIE</a> 

	behaviour to myself. </p>

	<h2><span class="mw-headline">History </span></h2>

	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn. </p>



</body>



</html>
